    cito:cites <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160836>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160840>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160828>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160847>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160845> ;
    dc:creator "Ratcliffe, Brett C.; Warner, William B." ;
    dc:title "Gymnetina howdeni Warner and Ratcliffe 2011, new species" ;
    trt:definesTaxonConcept <http://taxon-concept.plazi.org/id/Animalia/Gymnetina_howdeni_Ratcliffe_2011> ;
    trt:publishedIn <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160820> ;
    a trt:Treatment .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160820>
    bibo:endPage "28" ;
    bibo:issue "173" ;
    bibo:journal "Insecta Mundi" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2011-04-22" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "2011" ;
    dc:creator "Ratcliffe, Brett C.; Warner, William B." ;
    dc:date "2011" ;
    dc:title "A revision of the genus Gymnetina Casey, 1915 (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Cetoniinae: Gymnetini)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160836>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160840>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160828>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160847>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160845> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160836>
    dc:description "Figures 25-28. Gymnetina howdeni: 25a-b) Dorsal views, showing variation of cretaceous pattern on pronotum and elytra as well as sparse, small punctures on pronotal disc. 26) Oblique ventral view showing double row of cretaceous spots on sides of male abdomen, pygidial spot, and more broadly rounded apex of mesometasternal process. 27-28) Dorsal and ventral views, respectively, of parameres. Note distinct tooth at base of paramere on ventral side (arrow)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5160836/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160840>
    dc:description "Figure 32. Distribution map for Gymnetina species." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5160840/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160828>
    dc:description "Figures 11-14. Gymnetina cretacea cretacea: 11a-c) Dorsal views, showing variations of cretaceous pattern on pronotum, mesepimeron, and elytra as well as distinctive punctation on pronotum. 12) Lateral view showing cretaceous metepisternum, pygidial spot, flat mesometasternal process, single row of cretaceous spots on sides of abdomen and distinct concavity of male abdomen. 13-14) Dorsal and ventral views, respectively, of parameres. Note absence of tooth at base of paramere on ventral side (arrow)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5160828/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160847>
    dc:description "Figures 39-44. Habitats for Gymnetina species: 39) Huachuca Mts., Cochise Co,, AZ. 40) Oak woodland,east slope of Patagonia Mts. near Locheil, Santa Cruz Co., AZ. 41) Just southeast of Oaxaca, Mexico, habitat for Gymnetina alboscripta. 42) Baccharis sarothroides, Santa Cruz, Co., AZ. 43-44) Oak trees and tree holes in which Gymnetina species breed. Carr Canyon, Cochise Co., AZ." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5160847/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5160845>
    dc:description "Figures 33-38. Habitats for Gymnetina species: 33-34) Madera Canyon, Santa Cruz Co., AZ. 35) Cave Creek Canyon, Cochise Co., AZ. 36-37) Dragoon Mts., Cochise Co., AZ. 38) Patagonia Mts., Santa Cruz Co., AZ." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5160845/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

